classic-vibe-mac — third-party attribution
==========================================

This project bundles or downloads at build time the following third-party
artifacts. Each is used under its respective license; we make no
proprietary claim to any of them.

Apple Macintosh System 7.5.5
----------------------------

`scripts/build-boot-disk.sh` downloads a pre-installed, bootable
System 7.5.5 hard-disk image from the Internet Archive
(https://archive.org/details/macos755_202104) and modifies it in place
by adding our Minesweeper application into the System Folder's
Startup Items. The resulting image (`system755-vibe.dsk`) is published
alongside the rest of the static site.

System 7.5.3 was posted by Apple to its own support site in 2001 with a
license permitting free redistribution; the System 7.5.5 updater
(https://support.apple.com/kb/dl1099) released by Apple in 1996/1998
inherits the same redistribution posture (Apple has since taken the
legacy support pages offline, but the original licensing has not been
revoked, and major archives — Internet Archive, Macintosh Garden,
Macintosh Repository — distribute these binaries openly on this
basis). All copyrights in the underlying System 7.5.5 software remain
with Apple Inc.; classic-vibe-mac is not affiliated with or endorsed
by Apple.

If a successor in interest to this software contacts the maintainers
with a takedown request, we will remove the redistributed boot image
and document the path forward in LEARNINGS.md.

Infinite Mac (Apache-2.0)
-------------------------

`scripts/fetch-emulator.sh` downloads the BasiliskII Emscripten core
(`BasiliskII.js`, `BasiliskII.wasm`) from the Infinite Mac repository
(https://github.com/mihaip/infinite-mac), pinned to a specific commit.
Infinite Mac is licensed under Apache-2.0; the upstream LICENSE travels
with the binaries as `src/web/public/emulator/LICENSE-infinite-mac`.

`scripts/write-chunked-manifest.py` is an algorithmic port of
`write_chunked_image()` from
`mihaip/infinite-mac@30112da0db5d04ff5764d77ae757e73111a6ef12` ::
`scripts/import-disks.py`. The chunking parameters (256 KiB chunks,
blake2b-16 with salt b"raw") and JSON manifest shape match exactly so
the output is bit-compatible with the upstream worker
(`src/emulator/worker/chunked-disk.ts`).

BasiliskII / macemu (GPL-2.0)
-----------------------------

The BasiliskII WebAssembly binary downloaded by
`scripts/fetch-emulator.sh` is a derivative work of mihaip/macemu
(https://github.com/mihaip/macemu, GPL-2.0). Redistribution of the
.wasm therefore inherits GPL-2.0 obligations. See
`src/web/public/emulator/NOTICE` for the offer-source statement; the
source is the upstream macemu submodule referenced from the pinned
Infinite Mac commit.

Retro68 (CC0 / various)
-----------------------

The build pipeline cross-compiles our Mac app against the Retro68
toolchain (https://github.com/autc04/Retro68) via the rolling Docker
image `ghcr.io/autc04/retro68:latest`. Retro68 is composed of GCC
(GPL-3.0+ with exception), binutils, and runtime headers/libraries
under various permissive licenses. Retro68 itself is not redistributed
by classic-vibe-mac; we only consume it from CI containers.

hfsutils (GPL-2.0)
------------------

`scripts/build-disk-image.sh` and `scripts/build-boot-disk.sh` invoke
hfsutils (https://www.mars.org/home/rob/proj/hfs/), specifically the
`hformat`/`hmount`/`humount`/`hcopy`/`hmkdir`/`hattrib`/`hls`
binaries. hfsutils is GPL-2.0 and is installed in the build container
from Debian's `hfsutils` package; it is not redistributed by
classic-vibe-mac.
